<%#
# Text Form Partial

This partial renders a textarea element for a text attribute.

## Local variables:

- `f`:
  A Rails form generator, used to help create the appropriate input fields.
- `field`:
  An instance of [Administrate::Field::Text][1].
  A wrapper around the Text pulled from the database.

[1]: http://www.rubydoc.info/gems/administrate/Administrate/Field/Text
%>

<div class="field-unit__label">
  <%= f.label field.attribute %>
  Format text using <a href="https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet" target="_blank">Markdown</a>. Use the toolbar above the text field to format and preview.
</div>
<div class="field-unit__field">
  <%= f.text_area field.attribute, rows: 20, id: "markdown-text-area", "data-provide": "markdown" %>
</div>
